4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp that allows individuals to become cybersecurity specialists, even without previous knowledge. This program provides a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills in securing these environments. Participants will also learn about cloud security, penetration testing, cyber threat intelligence analysis, and risk management using data loss prevention strategies. The bootcamp lasts for 16 weeks and includes three live online classes per week. The class size is limited to 16 people. Upon completion, participants receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate recognized by multiple institutions. No previous experience is required to enroll in the bootcamp. Cybersecurity professionals in the United States earn a median annual salary of $103,560. For more information, visit the website: https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. stop